<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d179">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">603.4193/8–2351: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-28T20:00:00-04:00">August 28,
                                    1951—8 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1203. Ur 1007 Aug 23. Dept expects send msg (text in fol tel)<note n="1" xml:id="d179fn1">Telegram 1204 to London, August 28, was identical,
                                except for the last paragraph, to circular telegram 220, September
                                4, <ref target="#pg_1797">p. 1797</ref>.</note> re situation Amers
                            in China to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>s fol powers: Swed,
                            Nor, Den, Neth, Switz, Indo, Burm, India, Pak and USSR. Msg will go
                            concurrently with or soon after Brit note and memo, without ref to Brit
                            action. However, <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> may wish to
                            inform particular Govts it understands we are making separate
                            approach.</p>
                        <pb facs="0337" n="1795" xml:id="pg_1795"/>
                        <p>Dept appreciates and accepts offer <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> instr Brit missions collaborate with US colleagues
                            in various capitals.</p>
                        <p>If <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> has comment on our proposed
                            msg pls inform soonest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>